<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E82671317269D8745FB5AFDC2" author="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P." box="[943,1256,582,607]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="2439 - 2496" refId="ref51693" refString="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P. (2012 a) Taxonomic revision of the huntsman spider genus Eusparassus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Sparassidae) in Eurasia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 39 - 40, 2439 - 2496." type="journal article" year="2012">Moradmand &amp; Jäger 2012a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30465748267131725F58769FF7AFBBA" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8267131725F58769FBEFFD1E" blockId="68.[151,1436,438,643]" box="[199,1117,618,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725F58769FED2FD1F" bold="true" box="[199,352,618,643]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Distribution.</emphasis>
From the Middle East to Central and parts of South Asia (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A8267131726DD8769FBE2FD1E" box="[1007,1104,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="104.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[213,1363,195,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-41@104.[212,1363,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 72. Distribution range of (a) Eusparassus doriae group; (b) Eusparassus incertae sedis and Cercetius perezi. (a, b) with the same scale." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 72a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8267131725A587C8FDDBFD79" blockId="68.[151,617,715,741]" box="[151,617,715,741]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725A587C8FDDBFD79" bold="true" box="[151,617,715,741]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Species with unclear group affiliation</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136FF8267131725A58611FF7AFBBA" blockId="68.[151,1436,786,1062]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
The following three species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131724ED8610FCC3FCB6" authority="(Pocock, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[479,881,786,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131724ED8610FD09FCB6" box="[479,699,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus xerxes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E8267131727F98611FCDBFCB6" author="Pocock, R. I." box="[715,873,786,810]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="478 - 498" refId="ref52017" refString="Pocock, R. I. (1901) Descriptions of some new species of spiders from British India. Journal of Bombay Natural History Society, 13, 478 - 498." type="journal article" year="1901">Pocock, 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317264C8610FB1CFCB6" authority="Caporiacco, 1935" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[894,1198,786,810]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317264C8610FC6DFCB6" box="[894,991,787,810]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. pontii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E8267131726DA8611FB1CFCB6" author="Caporiacco, L. di" box="[1000,1198,786,810]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" refId="ref49970" refString="Caporiacco, L. di. (1935) Aracnidi dell'Himalaia e del Karakoram, raccolti dalla Missione italiana al Karakoram (1929 - VII). Memoire della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 13,161 - 263." type="book" year="1935">Caporiacco, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131721D48610FE95FCD2" authority="Simon, 1902" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1902" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Cercetius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezi">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131721D48610FA2EFCB6" box="[1254,1436,787,811]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Cercetius perezi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E8267131725A58635FE95FCD2" author="Simon, E." box="[151,295,822,846]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="252 - 254" refId="ref52657" refString="Simon, E. (1902) Arachnides recueillis au cours de la Mission de MM. J. Bonnier et Ch. Perez au Golfe Persique (Mars - Avril 1901). Bulletin du Museum d'historie naturelle (Paris), 8, 252 - 254." type="journal article" year="1902">Simon, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be placed in the species groups recognized above. They show a transition in character states. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131725A58658FEDFFCEE" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[151,365,859,882]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131725A58658FEDFFCEE" box="[151,365,859,882]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely allied to the members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131726028658FCCBFCEF" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[816,889,859,883]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131726028658FCCBFCEF" box="[816,889,859,883]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group but differ from them by having a distinct dark marking on the ventral opisthosoma (
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82671317274D867DFD52FC0A" box="[639,736,894,918]" captionStart="FIGURE 56" captionStartId="88.[151,250,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,194,1808]" captionTargetId="figure-74@88.[151,1436,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="88" captionText="FIGURE 56. Habitus and ventral views of Eusparassus spp. (a) Eusparassus educatus spec. nov. paratype male from Namibia; (b) Eusparassus tuckeri (Lawrence, 1927) comb. nov., female from Namibia; (c–d) Eusparassus xerxes (Pocock, 1901) (c syntype male from Pakistan, d syntype subadult male from Iran); (e–f) Eusparassus pontii Caporiacco, 1935, female from Ladakh, Himalayas, India." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 56f</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131727C6867CFC7EFC0A" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[756,972,895,918]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131727C6867CFC7EFC0A" box="[756,972,895,918]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Eusparassus pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131721AC867CFAB4FC0A" baseAuthorityName="Pocock" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[1182,1286,895,918]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xerxes">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131721AC867CFAB4FC0A" box="[1182,1286,895,918]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. xerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(presence of ventral opisthosoma marking) but differs by having a single bristle instead of four at the basal segment of the chelicerae. This species is probably derived from the members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C8267131726FE86C5FBA7FC42" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[972,1045,966,990]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doriae">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED8267131726FE86C5FBA7FC42" box="[972,1045,966,990]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">doriae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the Himalayas. For full description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D7C82671317240F86E8FE2DFB9E" authorityName="Caporiacco" authorityYear="1935" box="[317,415,1003,1026]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Eusparassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pontii">
<emphasis id="B96AEAED82671317240F86E8FE2DFB9E" box="[317,415,1003,1026]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">E. pontii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8F4B0E8267131724EE86E9FCABFB9E" author="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P." box="[476,793,1002,1027]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="2439 - 2496" refId="ref51693" refString="Moradmand, M. &amp; Jager, P. (2012 a) Taxonomic revision of the huntsman spider genus Eusparassus Simon, 1903 (Araneae: Sparassidae) in Eurasia. Journal of Natural History, 46, 39 - 40, 2439 - 2496." type="journal article" year="2012">Moradmand &amp; Jäger 2012a</bibRefCitation>
. The distribution of these three species is shown in 
<figureCitation id="13252A7A82671317204286E9FF76FBBA" captionStart="FIGURE 72" captionStartId="104.[151,250,1968,1991]" captionTargetBox="[213,1363,195,1941]" captionTargetId="figure-41@104.[212,1363,195,1942]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 72. Distribution range of (a) Eusparassus doriae group; (b) Eusparassus incertae sedis and Cercetius perezi. (a, b) with the same scale." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 72b</figureCitation>
.
